The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes a novel deep learning model based on generative adversarial networks (GANs) for synthesizing realistic person images. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also addresses the challenges of learning discriminative identity-sensitive and view-invariant features, which falls under the scope of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The proposed model generates images, which is a multimedia task, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with person re-identification, which is a task related to information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category.
